org.typemeta.funcj.functions

Interface FunctionsGenEx.F<A,R,X extends Exception>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the function argument type
    R - the function return type
    X - the exception type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FunctionsGenEx.Op<T,X>, FunctionsGenEx.Predicate<T,X>
    Enclosing class:
    FunctionsGenEx
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface FunctionsGenEx.F<A,R,X extends Exception>
    Function of arity 1. Note: if the input type to F is fixed to type T then the result is a monad, where pure = konst and bind = flatMap.
